'''
Templates
'''

* It's a convenient way to generate HTML in a dynamic way, they enable you to separate the design from the logic.
* Templates enable you to separate the design from the code.
* Logic templates can contain static parts of the desired HTML output,
  as well as some special syntax that describes how the dynamic content should be inserted.
* Django comes with its own template engine, and it is called Django template language.
* A Django project can be configured with one or more template engines.